        "author": "Christian Kadluba",
        "email": "10721825+ckadluba@users.noreply.github.com",
        "date": "2026-01-12T12:16:27Z",
        "message": "Merge pull request #660 from marcominerva/logevent-utc-timestamp\n\nFix UTC handling for TimeStamp column with ConvertToUtc=true",
        "url": "https://github.com/serilog-mssql/serilog-sinks-mssqlserver/commit/0da4b52dca2d09d9dd5f2edac28240d4c1cc5a25"
    },
    {
        "sha": "433e52bf0e3e7934eaeb8eb6301f9f073a878526",
        "author": "Marco Minerva",
        "email": "marco.minerva@gmail.com",
        "date": "2025-12-12T09:32:55Z",
        "message": "Fix UTC handling for TimeStamp column with ConvertToUtc=true\n\nPreviously, the TimeStamp column stored local DateTime values even when ConvertToUtc was enabled, unless the column type was DateTimeOffset. This change ensures that UtcDateTime is used when ConvertToUtc is true, so timestamps are always stored in UTC as intended. Adds a unit test (Bugfix #659) to verify correct UTC storage and DateTimeKind.",
        "url": "https://github.com/serilog-mssql/serilog-sinks-mssqlserver/commit/433e52bf0e3e7934eaeb8eb6301f9f073a878526"
    },
